commit.message:
Version 0.2.0. Two new fields were added: 'annotation' and 'seo keywords'.

You need run these alters to modify the schema:

    alter table dzenlog_text_textpost add `annotation` varchar(255) NOT NULL after generalpost_ptr_id;
    alter table dzenlog_text_textpost add `seo_keywords` varchar(255) NOT NULL;

comments.body:
Default TextMate function FTW. A few things you may want:
# The "new way" of doing classes is @class Tokenizer(object):@ . This is forward compatible;
# Make your file UTF-8 compatible (again, something coming soon) with a comment at the top of the file: @# encoding: utf-8@;
# You're mostly doing this already, but look at: <a href="http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/">PEP 8</a> for a nice default coding style.

